Recording of the "Demon Detour" live radio promo, broadcast on 46 different American radio stations throughout June 2005. Recording sessions actually took place across May 22-23. First performance with the Phase 2 band lineup. "All Alone" and "Clint Eastwood" from these sessions were later released as b-sides on the "Dirty Harry" and "DARE" singles, respectively. Portions of these sessions appear in the 2008 documentary "Bananaz". Unknown order.

First Gorillaz performance in North America and first show of the North American leg of the Debut Album Tour.  Damon played bass on some songs while other songs had no bass at all due to the band's bassist, Junior Dan, being arrested by American authorities upon landing for drugs and firearms charges from decades ago. A portion of this show is shown in the 2008 documentary "Bananaz".
